text.content: In "What to Do," Paul Graham discusses how individuals should live by creating good new things. He emphasizes that creation in fields like science and art is the pinnacle of human potential. While traditional virtues are important, contributing novel and valuable creations is essential for personal fulfillment and societal progress.
